libresidfp
------------------------------------------
This project is meant to replicate the SID as faithfully as possible while
keeping good performance for realtime use. It is not intended to expose the
chip internal state or adding fancy effects. Both the 6581 and the 8580 models
are emulated.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libresidfp-devel-1.1.1-1bl1
  libresidfp0-1.1.1-1bl1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/libsidplayfp/libresidfp

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/libsidplayfp/libresidfp/archive/refs/tags/v1.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libresidfp-1.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libresidfp-1.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libresidfp-1.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libresidfp-1.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libresidfp0-1.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libresidfp-devel-1.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libresidfp)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libresidfp.README
  /usr/share/doc/libresidfp/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libresidfp/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libresidfp/NEWS.md
  /usr/share/doc/libresidfp/README.md

(libresidfp0)
  /usr/bin/cygresidfp-0.dll

(libresidfp-devel)
  /usr/include/residfp/residfp.h
  /usr/include/residfp/residfp_defs.h
  /usr/include/residfp/sidversion.h
  /usr/lib/libresidfp.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libresidfp.pc

